Anglo American, Impala, Standard Bank: S. Africa Stock Preview

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-04-26T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/anglo-american-impala-standard-bank-may-move-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index rose for the third day
on April 21, gaining 0.4 percent to 32,658.86. South African
markets were closed on April 22 and April 25 for Easter.  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  : The diversified mining company
is in talks with Cia. Siderurgica Nacional SA and Grupo
Votorantim to sell its fertilizer unit Copebras SA, newspaper O
Estado de S. Paulo reported, citing an unidentified person with
knowledge of the transaction. Spokespeople at Anglo American,
CSN and Votorantim didn’t immediately return Bloomberg News
calls seeking comment. Anglo American gained 0.1 percent to
352.50 rand.  Anglo Platinum Ltd. (AMS)  : Platinum output in South
Africa, the biggest producer, will probably decline this year
because of safety stoppages and a lack of new projects,
Macquarie Group Ltd. said in an April 22 report. Anglo Platinum,
the largest producer of the white precious metal, rose 0.6
percent to 657.90 rand.  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  advanced
1.8 percent to 198.52 rand  Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): Africa’s largest bank
will hold talks with Turkish broker Standard Unlu, Bloomberg HT
reported. It would be a surprise should Standard Bank decide to
exit  Turkey , Standard Unlu general manager Atilla Koksal said,
according to the news channel. Ross Linstrom, a spokesman for
Johannesburg-based  Standard Bank , couldn’t immediately comment
when contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vernon Wessels in Johannesburg at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Riad Hamade at   rhamade@bloomberg.net  